definitions.definition: Unchanging ; that cannot or does not change .
Making no progress ; stalled, without movement or advancement.
Immobile ; fixed in place; having no motion .
Computed , created , or allocated before the program starts running, as opposed to at runtime .
Define d for the class itself, as opposed to instances of it; thus shared between all instances and accessible even without an instance.
